Tukur Muntari, Kano The COVID-19 Test Centre at the Mallam Aminu Kano Teaching Hospital, has received and treated 300 samples since its inception about two weeks ago. This figure was contained in a statement by the Assistant Director, Information and Public Affairs of the hospital, Hajiya Hauwa Mohammed and made available to newsmen in Kano on Monday. According to Mohammed, the Chief Medical Director of the hospital,  Prof. Abdurrahman Sheshe, made the disclosure while answering questions from newsmen at the board room of the hospital on Monday. “Three hundred samples were received and treated out of which many were COVID-19 negative while very few were positive. “At the moment, the centre receives samples from Katsina and Jigawa states in addition to the ones in Kano. “The hospital has also deployed some of its medical experts to all the isolation centers to assist in the fight against the pandemic disease,” she said. According to her,  the CMD had advised individuals coming to the test center to desist from coming to the laboratory demanding to be tested for COVID-19. He said the procedures of processing samples in the center was through the members of the NCDC. Copyright PUNCH.
